</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[187,1399,1796,1999]" lastBlockId="3.[188,1399,265,362]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[189,294,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,294,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Eulagius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky V." box="[542,784,1796,1823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="3 - 127" refId="ref6609" refString="Motschulsky V. 1845. Remarques sur la collection de Coleopteres russes de Victor de Motchoulsky. 1 er Article. Bulletin de la Societe imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 18 (1): 3 - 127." type="journal article" year="1845">Motschulsky (1845)</bibRefCitation>
for the Caucasian 
<taxonomicName authority="Motschulsky, 1845" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[1021,1394,1796,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acernus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1152,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. acernus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky V." box="[1164,1394,1796,1823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="3 - 127" refId="ref6609" refString="Motschulsky V. 1845. Remarques sur la collection de Coleopteres russes de Victor de Motchoulsky. 1 er Article. Bulletin de la Societe imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 18 (1): 3 - 127." type="journal article" year="1845">Motschulsky, 1845</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus seems characterized by an Asiatic chorotype (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Vigna Taglianti A. &amp; Audisio P. A. &amp; Biondi M. &amp; Bologna M. A. &amp; Carpaneto G. M. &amp; De Biase A. &amp; Fattorini S. &amp; Piattella E. &amp; Sindaco R. &amp; Venchi A. &amp; Zapparoli M." box="[939,1260,1831,1857]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="31 - 59" refId="ref7275" refString="Vigna Taglianti A., Audisio P. A., Biondi M., Bologna M. A., Carpaneto G. M., De Biase A., Fattorini S., Piattella E., Sindaco R., Venchi A. &amp; Zapparoli M. 1999. A proposal for a chorotype classification of the Near East fauna, in the framework of the Western Palearctic region. Biogeographia (n. s.) 20: 31 - 59." type="journal article" year="1999">
Vigna Taglianti 
<emphasis box="[1130,1191,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
), extending westwards to the Caucasian region. Eight species are currently ascribed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[1121,1226,1866,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1121,1226,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Eulagius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, five of them occurring in the eastern part of Palaearctic Asia, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reitter, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[877,1168,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[877,981,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. lewisi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[999,1159,1901,1927]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="264 - 266" refId="ref7023" refString="Reitter E. 1889. Ueber den Gattungsnamen Scydmaenus und Eumicrus. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1889 (2): 264 - 266." type="journal article" year="1889">Reitter, 1889</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lewis, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Lewis" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[1183,1299,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. reitteri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis G." pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="329 - 343" refId="ref6532" refString="Lewis G. 1896. On new species of Coleoptera from Japan, and notices of others. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (s. VI) 17 (101): 329 - 343." type="journal article" year="1896">Lewis, 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nikitsky, 1988" authorityName="Nikitsky" authorityYear="1988" box="[270,579,1936,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis box="[270,401,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. dentatus</emphasis>
Nikitsky, 1988
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nikitsky, 1988" authorityName="Nikitsky" authorityYear="1988" box="[586,929,1936,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[586,751,1937,1962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. ussuriensis</emphasis>
Nikitsky, 1988
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nikitsky, 1996" authorityName="Nikitsky" authorityYear="1996" box="[984,1305,1936,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis box="[984,1127,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. chinensis</emphasis>
Nikitsky, 1996
</taxonomicName>
, and the remaining three, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Motschulsky, 1845" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[476,832,1972,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acernus">
<emphasis box="[476,603,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. acernus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky V." box="[608,832,1972,1999]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="3 - 127" refId="ref6609" refString="Motschulsky V. 1845. Remarques sur la collection de Coleopteres russes de Victor de Motchoulsky. 1 er Article. Bulletin de la Societe imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 18 (1): 3 - 127." type="journal article" year="1845">Motschulsky, 1845</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reitter, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[841,1180,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis box="[841,1000,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. irregularis</emphasis>
(Reitter, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Esser, Varandi &amp; Farashiani, 2018" authorityName="Esser, Varandi &amp; Farashiani" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="64" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyrcanicus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1398,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. hyrcanicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Esser J. &amp; Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E." box="[189,588,265,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="239 - 243" refId="ref5890" refString="Esser J., Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E. 2018. A new species of Eulagius Motschulsky, 1845 (Coleoptera: Mycetophagidae) from Iran. Linzer biologische Beitrage 50 (1): 239 - 243." type="journal article" year="2018">Esser, Varandi &amp; Farashiani, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring between the Caucasus and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1134,1181,266,292]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Esser J. &amp; Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E." box="[1196,1394,265,291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="239 - 243" refId="ref5890" refString="Esser J., Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E. 2018. A new species of Eulagius Motschulsky, 1845 (Coleoptera: Mycetophagidae) from Iran. Linzer biologische Beitrage 50 (1): 239 - 243." type="journal article" year="2018">
Esser 
<emphasis box="[1266,1324,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky N. B." box="[188,361,300,326]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref6722" refString="Nikitsky N. B. 2020. Family Mycetophagidae Leach, 1915. In: Iwan D. &amp; Lobl I. (eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition: 27 - 33. Brill, Leiden / Boston." type="book chapter" year="2020">Nikitsky 2020</bibRefCitation>
). A ninth included species, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reitter 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[698,1094,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filicornis">
<emphasis box="[698,916,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Eulagius filicornis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[933,1085,300,326]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="71 - 100" refId="ref6866" refString="Reitter E. 1877. Atritomus nov. gen. Tritomidarum. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 21 (2): 384. Reitter E. 1879. Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren. I. Enthaltend die Familien: Cucujidae, Telmatophilidae, Tritomidae, Mycetaeidae, Endomychidae, Lyctidae und Sphindidae. Verhandlungen der kaiserlich-koniglichen zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 21: 71 - 100." type="journal article" year="1877">Reitter 1877</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
” (described in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1877" box="[1274,1390,301,327]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1390,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Atritomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[189,338,335,362]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="71 - 100" refId="ref6866" refString="Reitter E. 1877. Atritomus nov. gen. Tritomidarum. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 21 (2): 384. Reitter E. 1879. Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren. I. Enthaltend die Familien: Cucujidae, Telmatophilidae, Tritomidae, Mycetaeidae, Endomychidae, Lyctidae und Sphindidae. Verhandlungen der kaiserlich-koniglichen zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 21: 71 - 100." type="journal article" year="1877">Reitter 1877</bibRefCitation>
b), is transferred to a separate, new genus described hereunder.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,401,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
It should also be noted that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lewis" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[522,718,401,427]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[522,718,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Eulagius reitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in 1896 and not in 1895 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis G." box="[1251,1394,401,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="329 - 343" refId="ref6532" refString="Lewis G. 1896. On new species of Coleoptera from Japan, and notices of others. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (s. VI) 17 (101): 329 - 343." type="journal article" year="1896">Lewis 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Esser J. &amp; Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E." box="[190,391,436,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="239 - 243" refId="ref5890" refString="Esser J., Varandi H. B. &amp; Farashiani M. E. 2018. A new species of Eulagius Motschulsky, 1845 (Coleoptera: Mycetophagidae) from Iran. Linzer biologische Beitrage 50 (1): 239 - 243." type="journal article" year="2018">
Esser 
<emphasis box="[260,319,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
